My lads are pretty simple I have a setup with earthworms and springtails in some eco earth and I don't really need to do soil changes since the bioactive part handles it well. I spent about $30 on eco earth bricks and the worms / springtails and a couple plants (but toads just. destroy plants. its not worth it if you aren't ready to lose them), and a big fancy hide was $20.
